1. Introduction to SVG
- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/SVG
- you can embed directly into html or add with img or background url
- img(src='img/star.svg' alt='Star Logo')
- background: transparent url('../img/star.svg') center center no-repeat

2. SVG and CSS
- .svg { }
- ... 
- .circle { fill: blue }
- it's best to use svg with img and only embed them when you must apply styling
- stroke-opacity: 0; stroke-width: 8; // less detail and larger stroke width on mobile first
- fine detail is not always visible on smaller screen resolutions
- add detail as the screen gets larger
